    "There were four false positives (samples incorrectly labeled as \"artefact\") that originated from \"normal\" conditions.",
    "A further 12 \"normal\" samples were incorrectly labeled as \"exstole\" (false positives).",
    "There were 35 false positives (samples incorrectly labeled as \"extrastole\") among the \"normal\" group.",
    "In total, 32 \"normal\" samples were incorrectly labeled as \"murmur\" (false positives).",
    "Elements of the confusion matrix that fall on the diagonal reflect correctly categorized samples (true positives) for each class."
